Question 2.5.2 (Counter example to Totally Asynchronous Convergence by Gradient Method)

Function: f(x) = (1/2)*x'*Q*x + b'*x

Constraint: Q = | 1+c    1     1  |
                |  1    1+c    1  |
                |  1     1    1+c |

            where 0 < c < 1

A sequence of iterates generated by the algorithm in Example 2.5.1 where x0 = 1:

          f(x) = (1/2)*x'*Q*x + b'*x

          delf(x) = Q*x + b

          x^{k+1} = x^k - alpha*delf(x^k)

                  = (1-alpha*Q)*x^k - alpha*b

          eta_i*(1-alpha*Q) + alpha*sum_i_n[eta_i*Q] < eta_i

          eta_i*Q > sum_i_n[eta_i*Q]

          0 < alpha < min [2*eta_i/(eta_i*(1-alpha*Q) + alpha*sum_i_n[eta_i*Q])] 

          x^1 = (1-alpha*Q)*x^0 - alpha*b

              = (1-(c^3+3*c^2)/(2*c^3)) - b/(2*c^3)

          x^2 = (1-alpha*Q)*x^1 - alpha*b

              = ...

Rules: Gradient Method:
         x^{k+1} = x^k - alpha*delf(x^k)
